<title>USA: KPMG Peat Marwick LLP names Stephen Butler CEO.</title>
<headline>KPMG Peat Marwick LLP names Stephen Butler CEO.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-04</dateline>
<text>
<p>KPMG Peat Marwick LLP said on Friday that Stephen Butler had been elected chairman and chief executive and Roger Siboni had been elected deputy chairman, effectively immediately.</p>
<p>Both were elected for six-year terms, the company said.</p>
<p>Butler, formerly partner-in-charge of KPMG's financial services practice in New York, succeeds Jon Madonna, who will become chairman of KPMG International.</p>
<p>Siboni succeeds James Brocksmith.</p>
<p>Both former officers' terms expired, the company said.</p>
